				=09
					=09

<div class=3D"paragraph" style=3D"text-align:justify;"><font size=3D"4"><u>=
<font color=3D"#f8a9a9"><strong>2 x 2 Example</strong></font></u></font><br=
><span></span>We shall encrypt the plaintext message "short example" using =
the keyword <em>hill</em> and a 2 x 2 matrix. The first step is to turn the=
 keyword into a matrix. If the keyword was longer than the 4 letters needed=
, we would only take the first 4 letters, and if it was shorter, we would f=
ill it up with the alphabet in order (much like a <a title=3D"" href=3D"htt=
ps://crypto.interactive-maths.com/mixed-alphabet-cipher.html">Mixed Alphabe=
t</a>).<br></div>


				=09
				</td>				<td class=3D"wsite-multicol-col" style=3D"width:27.60563380281=
7%; padding:0 15px;">
				=09
					=09

<div><div class=3D"wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style=3D"padding-t=
