227655_orig.jpg" alt=3D"Picture" style=3D"width:100%;max-width:782px">
</a>
<div style=3D"display:block;font-size:90%">Multiplying the multiplicative i=
nverse of the determinant by the adjugate to get the inverse key matrix.=20
NB - note that the 165 should read 105.</div>
</div></div>

<div class=3D"paragraph" style=3D"text-align:left;">That is:<br></div>

<div><div class=3D"wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style=3D"padding-t=
op:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:center"=
>
<a>
<img src=3D"https://crypto.interactive-maths.com/uploads/1/1/3/4/11345755/5=
539883_orig.jpg" alt=3D"Picture" style=3D"width:100%;max-width:624px">
</a>
<div style=3D"display:block;font-size:90%"></div>
</div></div>

<div class=3D"paragraph" style=3D"text-align:justify;">Now we have the inve=
rse key matrix, we have to convert the ciphertext into column vectors and m=
ultiply the inverse matrix by each column vector in turn, take the results =
modulo 26 and convert these back into letters to get the plaintext.<br></di=
v>

