<font color=3D"#f8a9a9"><strong>3 x 3 Example</strong></font></u></font><br=
><span></span>We shall decrypt the ciphertext message "SYICHOLER" using the=
 keyword <em>alphabet</em>. The first step is to turn the key phrase into a=
 matrix. Notice that the keyword is a letter short, so we fill in the final=
 element with the start of the alphabet. Now we need to convert this into t=
he inverse key matrix, following the same step as for a 2 x 2 matrix. Howev=
er, the way we calculate each step is slightly different.<br></div>


				=09
